   1. Running Simultaneously: Only one program can "listen" to a port at a time. If your original app is running on port 3002, the backup's backend will fail to start because the port is already taken. If they have different ports, you can run both versions at the same
      time to compare them.
   2. Data Isolation: The backend is what saves your files, snapshots, and insights. If both apps share one backend, any "mobile addition" that changes how data is saved might accidentally overwrite or corrupt the "perfect" data in your desktop version.

  By giving the backup its own backend on port 3004, it becomes a complete, independent clone. You can break things in the backup/mobile version as much as you want, and your "perfect" desktop data will remain 100% untouched.

